WEBVTT

00:00.671 --> 00:01.978
Previously on...

00:02.001 --> 00:03.980
It seems on
his last three trips east,

00:04.003 --> 00:05.657
he cashed in
his first-class ticket

00:05.681 --> 00:07.384
and took a detour
to Atlantic city.

00:07.408 --> 00:10.157
Lynette received
some disturbing news...

00:10.181 --> 00:14.165
He said it was okay for me to kiss
her. What else did your brother tell you?

00:14.189 --> 00:15.415
Caleb revealed a secret...

00:17.118 --> 00:20.697
Susan made
a first class confession...

00:20.721 --> 00:23.570
You're going to leave me out
here in the middle of nowhere?

00:23.594 --> 00:26.108
I can't be around you anymore.
I'm just not strong enough.

00:26.132 --> 00:28.235
And Bree made
the most difficult decision

00:28.259 --> 00:30.759
of her life.

00:35.266 --> 00:37.244
Susan Mayer
had always believed

00:37.268 --> 00:40.347
the one good thing
about hard times

00:40.371 --> 00:44.791
is that you get to find out
who your friends really are.

00:44.815 --> 00:47.194
When her grandmother died,

00:47.218 --> 00:50.097
it was Bree who brought
homemade cookies.

00:50.121 --> 00:52.699
When the critics
panned her third book,

00:52.723 --> 00:56.463
it was Gabrielle who hired
the handsome masseur.

00:56.487 --> 00:59.206
When her divorce became final,

00:59.230 --> 01:03.270
it was Lynette who poured
the scotch.

01:03.294 --> 01:07.614
Sadly, Susan's life had been
shattered once again...

01:07.638 --> 01:09.616
But as always,

01:09.640 --> 01:13.650
her friends had come to help
pick up the pieces.

01:13.674 --> 01:17.384
Susan? We've all been talking.

01:17.408 --> 01:20.457
We've decided you and Julie
should stay with Bree.

01:20.481 --> 01:23.059
Oh, thanks. No, that's okay.
We'll stay at a motel.

01:23.083 --> 01:24.461
Absolutely not.

01:24.485 --> 01:27.734
Just give me an hour or two
to straighten up Andrew's room,

01:27.758 --> 01:30.497
and then you can bring
your... selves over.

01:30.521 --> 01:32.269
I don't deserve friends
like you.

01:32.293 --> 01:33.770
We're aware of that.

01:35.126 --> 01:37.404
Susan, you're running low
on trash bags.

01:37.428 --> 01:39.406
I'm going to run to the store.

01:39.430 --> 01:41.408
Thanks, Orson.
Thanks for coming.

01:41.432 --> 01:43.780
You know,
you didn't have to do this.

01:43.804 --> 01:45.384
Hey, it's my pleasure.

01:50.211 --> 01:52.111
Mrs. Mayer!

01:54.885 --> 01:57.224
Hi. Bud penrod,

01:57.248 --> 02:00.597
town and country insurance...
The "can-do" people.

02:00.621 --> 02:03.099
Oh, it's nice to meet you.

02:03.123 --> 02:04.401
Yeah. Look at that.

02:04.425 --> 02:06.833
Well, that's no fun at all,
is it?

02:06.857 --> 02:08.335
No. No, it isn't.

02:08.359 --> 02:11.138
So when am I gonna get
the check?

02:11.162 --> 02:12.739
'Cause I have a lot
of rebuilding to do.

02:12.763 --> 02:14.741
I need to get started.

02:14.765 --> 02:17.244
Yeah, well, I'm afraid
that's going to be a while.

02:17.268 --> 02:20.347
You see, the fire department
has ruled that this was arson.

02:20.371 --> 02:21.688
Arson?

02:21.712 --> 02:24.291
Yeah. So we can't give you
any money

02:24.315 --> 02:25.592
until we finish
our investigation.

02:25.616 --> 02:27.454
Who would wanna burn down
my house?

02:27.478 --> 02:30.227
I don't know.
Do you have any enemies?

02:30.251 --> 02:32.529
No. No, lookit.

02:32.553 --> 02:35.762
The whole neighborhood
turned out to help.

02:35.786 --> 02:37.564
I'm very popular.

02:37.588 --> 02:41.168
And there's no one among them
that wishes you ill?

02:41.192 --> 02:44.471
Oh, no, no.
Everybody's been very helpful.

02:44.495 --> 02:47.565
Um, everybody likes me.
Absolutely...

02:50.601 --> 02:51.818
Everyone.

02:51.842 --> 02:55.151
Yes, hard times
were what Susan used

02:55.175 --> 02:57.284
to distinguish who was a friend

02:57.308 --> 03:05.308
and who wasn't.

03:07.918 --> 03:11.338
Not everyone enjoys
being a small part

03:11.362 --> 03:12.639
of a large community.

03:12.663 --> 03:16.343
Indeed, some yearn to leave
the stress and noise

03:16.367 --> 03:19.175
of constant companionship
behind them,

03:19.199 --> 03:21.177
so they strike out on their own,

03:21.201 --> 03:25.181
hoping their solitude will
bring a little peace and quiet.

03:25.205 --> 03:28.255
It's only then they discover

03:28.279 --> 03:30.757
how dangerous it is...

03:30.781 --> 03:34.391
To be alone in the world.

04:05.416 --> 04:08.355
Zach, did you get the trash?

04:08.379 --> 04:10.627
How'd you get in here?

04:10.651 --> 04:11.858
Hiya, Paul.

04:11.882 --> 04:14.361
I stood at the back door
shouting and shouting.

04:14.385 --> 04:16.333
Were you in the little boys
room? I'm calling the police.

04:16.357 --> 04:17.964
No need. I just needed
to borrow some flour.

04:17.988 --> 04:19.536
I'm a little bit psychic,

04:19.560 --> 04:22.539
and I predict fresh-baked
cookies in your future.

04:22.563 --> 04:24.541
Zachary.

04:24.565 --> 04:26.313
What'd she want?

04:26.337 --> 04:27.774
She was in the cupboard.

04:27.798 --> 04:30.277
Get a trash bag.
We're throwing everything away.

04:30.301 --> 04:32.519
You think she was trying
to poison us?

04:32.543 --> 04:37.013
All I know is
we're eating out tonight.

04:41.352 --> 04:43.330
What doyouwant?

04:43.354 --> 04:47.464
Uh... this is a little awkward,
and I apologize in advance

04:47.488 --> 04:51.768
for how this is gonna sound,
but, um...

04:51.792 --> 04:56.042
By any chance,
did... you burn down my house?

04:56.066 --> 04:58.345
Yes.

04:58.369 --> 05:02.879
What? Yes, I burnt down your house,
you sleazy little whore.

05:02.903 --> 05:06.052
Edie! Why would you do that?!

05:06.076 --> 05:07.554
Can you blame me,

05:07.578 --> 05:10.717
after sending me
that acid letter?

05:10.741 --> 05:12.959
Letter? What letter?

05:12.983 --> 05:15.970
The one where you admitted
to stabbing me in the back

05:15.994 --> 05:17.664
by sleeping with Karl.

05:17.688 --> 05:19.295
You weren't supposed
to get that.

05:19.319 --> 05:21.297
I stole that back
from the mailman.

05:21.321 --> 05:23.630
So you were trying to hide
the truth from me?

05:23.654 --> 05:26.933
This is not what
we should focus on right now.

05:26.957 --> 05:29.836
The point is, you maliciously
set fire to my house.

05:29.860 --> 05:33.480
Look, I admit I might have...
Overreacted a tad.

05:33.504 --> 05:35.482
A tad? Edie, I have no roof!

05:35.506 --> 05:37.784
You can't just go around
burning down people's homes.

05:37.808 --> 05:40.987
Why not? You burnt down my home.

05:41.011 --> 05:43.850
You stole Mike from me.
You slept with my fiancÃ©.

05:43.874 --> 05:45.352
That's the trifecta.

05:45.376 --> 05:47.354
You're lucky
I didn't torch your car.

05:47.378 --> 05:49.356
That's it.
I'm going to the police,

05:49.380 --> 05:51.428
and I'm telling them
what you did.

05:51.452 --> 05:53.760
Did what? I didn't do anything.

05:53.784 --> 05:56.332
What? You just confessed.

05:56.356 --> 05:57.834
No, I didn't.

05:57.858 --> 06:01.007
Did anyone else hear me confess?

06:01.031 --> 06:02.509
Hello?

06:02.533 --> 06:04.441
Hello?

06:04.465 --> 06:06.495
No witnesses.

06:07.468 --> 06:09.946
No evidence, no confession.

06:09.970 --> 06:11.848
I guess we're done here.

06:11.872 --> 06:13.850
You can go home now.

06:13.874 --> 06:15.361
Oh, wait. That's right.

06:15.385 --> 06:17.424
You don't have one.

06:25.786 --> 06:29.396
No, no, xiao-Mei,
I've told you a million times.

06:29.420 --> 06:31.398
No red meat for Mr. Solis.

06:31.422 --> 06:33.099
My triglycerides
are through the roof.

06:33.123 --> 06:36.033
Mm. Sweetie,
I need some more cream.

06:42.973 --> 06:44.943
Xiao-Mei, what's wrong?

06:47.438 --> 06:48.915
She smell.

06:48.939 --> 06:50.487
Who smells? Gaby?

06:50.511 --> 06:52.559
Excuse me. What?

06:52.583 --> 06:56.463
Her perfume... Make me sick.

06:56.487 --> 06:58.465
Honey, it's 100 bucks an ounce.

06:58.489 --> 07:00.967
That tends to make everyone
a little nauseous.

07:00.991 --> 07:03.970
Xiao-Mei, your boobs...
Are they tender?

07:03.994 --> 07:05.872
Mm-hmm.

07:05.896 --> 07:08.635
Carlos! Her boobs
are none of your business.

07:08.659 --> 07:11.738
Gaby, think.
She's sensitive to smell,

07:11.762 --> 07:14.572
nauseous
and has swollen breasts.

07:26.446 --> 07:28.655
Well, I just ran her blood work.

07:28.679 --> 07:31.427
It looks like the insemination
was successful.

07:31.451 --> 07:32.428
Oh!

07:32.452 --> 07:34.931
Oh, my god.
We're gonna have a baby!

07:34.955 --> 07:36.503
Now, you should know,

07:36.527 --> 07:38.505
since she's experiencing
early symptoms,

07:38.529 --> 07:40.707
this might be
a tough pregnancy for her.

07:40.731 --> 07:43.470
Not a problem. We are gonna
treat her like a queen!

07:43.494 --> 07:46.621
Absolutely. You have nothing
to worry about here.

07:48.739 --> 07:51.548
Oh, Mrs. Solis, you smell.

07:51.572 --> 07:53.672
Oh, yeah. Okay. Sorry.

07:59.650 --> 08:01.457
I think it's gonna be a kick

08:01.481 --> 08:03.459
having Susan and Julie
stay with us.

08:03.483 --> 08:05.537
It'll be like living
in a sorority.

08:05.561 --> 08:08.635
We'll stay up late and we'll
gossip and make s'mores.

08:08.659 --> 08:10.767
Doesn't that sound like fun?

08:10.791 --> 08:14.470
Why are you pretending
to be happy?

08:14.494 --> 08:17.481
I heard you walking around
your room all night long...

08:17.505 --> 08:18.705
Crying.

08:18.729 --> 08:21.978
I don't want to talk about it.

08:22.002 --> 08:23.980
Look, I know why you're worried,

08:24.004 --> 08:27.584
but Andrew can take care
of himself, and if he can't,

08:27.608 --> 08:29.886
he shouldn't have run away
in the first place.

08:29.910 --> 08:32.958
You know what? Maybe Andrew
leaving will be good for us.

08:32.982 --> 08:36.222
You are all I have left,
and I am gonna be

08:36.246 --> 08:38.794
the best mother that I can be.

08:38.818 --> 08:40.649
There's definitely
room for improvement.

08:42.052 --> 08:44.971
It's just...

08:44.995 --> 08:47.674
You kinda forgot my birthday.

08:47.698 --> 08:50.136
What?

08:50.160 --> 08:53.610
Yeah. It was six weeks ago.

08:53.634 --> 08:57.013
Oh, my god, Danielle.
I am so sorry.

08:57.037 --> 08:59.686
It's okay.
You had a lot going on.

08:59.710 --> 09:01.688
I mean, Andrew was suing you,

09:01.712 --> 09:04.150
and you were pretty wasted
that month.

09:04.174 --> 09:07.158
Honey, you've gotta let me
make it up to you.

09:07.182 --> 09:09.155
I-I'm gonna throw you
a birthday party

09:09.179 --> 09:11.157
with all your friends, okay?

09:11.181 --> 09:13.581
That could be cool.

09:15.055 --> 09:16.933
You know what else I'd like?

09:16.957 --> 09:18.565
Name it. It's yours.

09:18.589 --> 09:20.889
I want Andrew's room.

09:22.693 --> 09:24.680
You said he's probably
not coming back,

09:24.704 --> 09:27.944
and I could really use
the extra closet space.

09:27.968 --> 09:30.717
But, sweetheart, this is...
This is his room.

09:30.741 --> 09:33.149
Mom, you forgot my birthday.

09:33.173 --> 09:35.687
You're really in no position
to negotiate.

09:35.711 --> 09:38.655
Honey, where am I gonna put
all of his things?

09:38.679 --> 09:41.658
And, you know, he might
come back at some point.

09:41.682 --> 09:43.830
He won't.

09:43.854 --> 09:47.764
Like you said,
I'm all you have left.

09:50.791 --> 09:52.298
Atlantic city?

09:52.322 --> 09:53.800
Yeah, it's last minute,

09:53.824 --> 09:55.981
but Jerry got a great deal on
a suite at one of the casinos,

09:56.005 --> 09:58.975
and a bunch of the old gang
is coming in from New York,

09:58.999 --> 10:00.977
and god, it's been forever
since I have been,

10:01.001 --> 10:02.849
so how could I turn that down?

10:02.873 --> 10:04.651
Yeah, how, indeed?

10:04.675 --> 10:06.653
What?

10:06.677 --> 10:08.715
I didn't say anything.

10:08.739 --> 10:10.787
No, but you have that look.

10:10.811 --> 10:12.689
Is something wrong?

10:12.713 --> 10:14.793
No!

10:17.117 --> 10:19.595
Except that I know you've been
to Atlantic city

10:19.619 --> 10:22.999
three times in the last month
without telling me.

10:23.023 --> 10:26.007
Ed found the receipts
when he did the office audit.

10:26.031 --> 10:27.974
Other than that,
no, nothing's wrong.

10:29.259 --> 10:31.738
Tom, it would be better
for your general well-being

10:31.762 --> 10:34.080
if you did not laugh
at this moment in time.

10:34.104 --> 10:36.087
Am I gonna have to ruin
the surprise?

10:36.111 --> 10:38.144
Because
it's a really good surprise.

10:38.168 --> 10:40.216
I'm thinking, yeah, ruin it.

10:40.240 --> 10:42.719
I have been going to
Atlantic city for business.

10:42.743 --> 10:44.860
I am up for a top spot
with Jerry's firm,

10:44.884 --> 10:47.093
huffington promotions.

10:47.117 --> 10:49.117
And if you don't believe me...

10:51.051 --> 10:55.261
You can call the c.E.O. Himself.

10:55.285 --> 11:01.267
I am... so happy
and I'm so relieved.

11:01.291 --> 11:04.240
Did you think I was cheating?

11:04.264 --> 11:06.813
No! Absolutely not. Lynette...

11:06.837 --> 11:08.675
No! Okay, a little bit.

11:08.699 --> 11:10.977
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

11:11.001 --> 11:13.680
Ed found receipts for flowers
and theater tickets.

11:13.704 --> 11:16.931
I mean, by the way, did you...
Jerry and I went to a show,

11:16.955 --> 11:19.655
and the flowers
were for milt's wife.

11:19.679 --> 11:22.328
I knew that. You didn't
have to tell me that.

11:22.352 --> 11:24.769
Why did you buy flowers
for milt's wife? Lynette...

11:24.793 --> 11:28.664
Sorry. Stop. Done talking.
That's fantastic.

11:28.688 --> 11:30.697
I love you!

11:30.721 --> 11:32.121
I love you.

11:53.343 --> 11:54.753
Carlos...

11:57.417 --> 11:59.195
What's going on?

11:59.219 --> 12:01.097
Xiao-Mei is feeling
under the weather,

12:01.121 --> 12:03.800
so I took up the vacuuming.

12:03.824 --> 12:05.807
Oh, well,
I'm sorry to hear that.

12:05.831 --> 12:07.874
So, uh, did you move
my beauty products?

12:07.898 --> 12:10.898
They're not in the bathroom.

12:11.962 --> 12:13.439
Why in the hell?

12:13.463 --> 12:17.320
I forgot to tell you. Uh, you
can't use that stuff anymore.

12:17.344 --> 12:20.817
It really triggers
xiao-Mei's morning sickness.

12:20.841 --> 12:24.320
All of it? Even my hair pomade?

12:24.344 --> 12:27.428
Gives me stomachache. Yeah,
well, it gives me volume,

12:27.452 --> 12:30.056
so I guess we're both
gonna have a problem.

12:30.080 --> 12:32.458
Do you have to be
so high-maintenance?

12:32.482 --> 12:35.869
You're not a model, Carlos.
Maintenance is my only skill.

12:35.893 --> 12:37.934
Please, no fight.

12:37.958 --> 12:41.458
If Mrs. Solis smell bad,
I be okay.

12:43.363 --> 12:48.214
Fine. I'll learn
to live without product.

12:48.238 --> 12:50.917
But when my hair
starts smelling like hair,

12:50.941 --> 12:52.941
I don't wanna hear a word.

12:55.846 --> 12:58.354
Surprise!

12:58.378 --> 13:00.256
What the hell is that?

13:00.280 --> 13:02.929
Isn't it darling?
I made it for your party.

13:02.953 --> 13:04.940
It's a big "1" and a big "7"...

13:06.056 --> 13:07.093
For "17."

13:07.117 --> 13:09.996
Were you up all night
making that thing?

13:10.020 --> 13:11.898
Yeah. I just wasn't tired.

13:11.922 --> 13:14.200
Oh, I wanna show you
what else I've planned.

13:14.224 --> 13:16.402
I think you're gonna love it.

13:16.426 --> 13:18.905
You got a fajita bar
and a juggler?

13:18.929 --> 13:20.546
No, relax.
He's a very hip juggler.

13:20.570 --> 13:22.879
He only performs
to Beatles songs,

13:22.903 --> 13:25.186
and I saw the video,
and it's absolutely thrilling.

13:25.210 --> 13:27.513
Mom, I don't want
any of this stuff.

13:27.537 --> 13:31.057
It's not even my real birthday. Danielle,
I just want you to have the best party

13:31.081 --> 13:33.059
you have ever had
in your entire life.

13:33.083 --> 13:35.930
I just want a few friends
to come over and hang out.

13:35.954 --> 13:37.463
You can make a cake,

13:37.487 --> 13:38.965
but giant balloon numbers?

13:38.989 --> 13:42.268
I mean, come on.
They would all make fun of me.

13:42.292 --> 13:45.602
Oh.

13:47.827 --> 13:49.827
Okay.

13:56.937 --> 13:58.484
Is that really necessary?

13:58.508 --> 14:01.908
Honey, I can't possibly
put it in the garbage as is.

14:06.977 --> 14:09.555
It's just another morning
with the Van de kamps.

14:09.579 --> 14:11.827
Oh, Susan, did I wake you?

14:11.851 --> 14:14.360
Uh, no. No, I was up.

14:14.384 --> 14:16.367
Well, I'm sorry about the noise.

14:16.391 --> 14:18.865
It's just that Danielle
doesn't want balloons,

14:18.889 --> 14:20.867
and I'm kind of pressed
for time.

14:20.891 --> 14:25.341
Bree... are you okay?

14:26.866 --> 14:29.345
She said she doesn't
want balloons.

14:29.369 --> 14:32.199
I'm fine.

14:42.112 --> 14:44.190
Mom?

14:44.214 --> 14:48.094
Look, I know you're out there.
Please, just talk to me.

14:48.118 --> 14:50.566
Mom, I need something to drink.

14:50.590 --> 14:53.869
Just some water, some juice.
Something, anything. Please.

14:53.893 --> 14:55.903
Mom!

14:59.970 --> 15:03.509
You want me to say
that I set Caleb up?

15:03.533 --> 15:06.913
Yeah, I did it.

15:08.578 --> 15:11.057
I started thinking
about all those years...

15:11.081 --> 15:14.160
Years that we had
to take care of him, and...

15:14.184 --> 15:16.993
I just thought
maybe once he was gone,

15:17.017 --> 15:19.125
we could have a normal life.

15:19.149 --> 15:23.029
And I'm sorry.

15:23.053 --> 15:26.340
But, mom, you have got
to let me out of here now.

15:26.364 --> 15:29.635
Damn you!

15:29.659 --> 15:31.637
You were willing to stand by

15:31.661 --> 15:35.481
and let me murder your brother
without reason.

15:35.505 --> 15:38.184
That's an unforgivable betrayal.

15:38.208 --> 15:41.017
I am so consumed with rage.

15:41.041 --> 15:44.020
It's best you stay in there,
because if I let you out,

15:44.044 --> 15:48.324
I don't know what
I might do to you.

15:56.956 --> 15:58.334
Hello?

15:58.358 --> 16:00.336
I need Edie to spill her guts.

16:00.360 --> 16:02.360
What do you know
about wearing a wire?

16:03.733 --> 16:05.616
So you see the
little red light? Mm.

16:05.640 --> 16:07.113
It's all voice-activated,

16:07.137 --> 16:09.115
so if the light's on,
you're recording.

16:09.139 --> 16:11.617
Uh, let me show you
how to tape it on.

16:11.641 --> 16:13.449
Oh, okay.

16:13.473 --> 16:15.451
Sorry if my hands are cold.

16:15.475 --> 16:19.405
Um... no, that's okay.
They're fine.

16:23.683 --> 16:26.232
So you sure you wanna do this?

16:26.256 --> 16:28.394
Yeah. I'm sort of
up against the wall.

16:28.418 --> 16:30.396
The insurance company
needs proof fast,

16:30.420 --> 16:33.099
and things are sort of weird
at Bree's.

16:33.123 --> 16:35.280
I don't wanna overstay
my welcome.

16:35.304 --> 16:40.246
Well, if things get tough,
you can always stay here.

16:40.270 --> 16:42.048
Testing, testing.

16:42.072 --> 16:46.052
I'm sorry. Did you just
invite me to move in with you?

16:46.076 --> 16:48.654
Well, you and Julie
in the spare bedroom.

16:48.678 --> 16:50.016
Oh.

16:50.040 --> 16:51.687
You've...

16:51.711 --> 16:54.690
You've been saying how
you want to be friends again,

16:54.714 --> 16:56.192
and you're right.

16:56.216 --> 16:59.695
There's no reason
we can't be friends.

16:59.719 --> 17:03.369
You sure that won't put a crimp
in your, uh, dating life?

17:03.393 --> 17:07.103
You know, that girl
you were at the movies with?

17:07.127 --> 17:08.773
No. That was a one-time thing.

17:08.798 --> 17:12.078
But what about that guy,
though? Orson.

17:12.102 --> 17:16.112
Yeah, he just heard about
the fire and came over to help.

17:16.136 --> 17:17.242
We're friends.

17:17.267 --> 17:20.586
Oh. So... neither of us
is dating anybody.

17:20.609 --> 17:23.069
Guess not.

17:26.415 --> 17:29.395
I got my boarding pass.

17:29.419 --> 17:32.228
Do what you need to do
and don't worry about the kids.

17:32.252 --> 17:34.230
I'll keep 'em out of trouble.

17:34.254 --> 17:35.731
Is this crazy?

17:35.755 --> 17:38.033
Following Tom across the country
just to spy on him?

17:38.057 --> 17:40.035
If he knew I was doing this...

17:40.059 --> 17:43.109
God, I don't think
I can go through with this.

17:43.133 --> 17:45.150
Now, look, there's probably
nothing going on,

17:45.174 --> 17:48.114
but you need to know the truth.

17:48.138 --> 17:49.415
Do I? I'm happy.

17:49.439 --> 17:52.278
I mean, I was. Why don't I
just look the other way

17:52.302 --> 17:55.286
and pretend nothing's wrong?
Lots of women can do that.

17:55.310 --> 17:57.323
But we both know
you're not one of them.

17:57.347 --> 18:01.147
And what if I see him
with another woman? What then?

18:03.683 --> 18:06.123
I own a gun.

