Is she serious?

19:49.489 --> 19:51.789
Welcome to my own private hell.

19:55.665 --> 19:58.374
That is some serious frosting.

19:58.398 --> 20:00.198
All righty.

20:15.345 --> 20:17.923
Who touched this?

20:17.947 --> 20:21.196
Mom, what is the matter?
It's just a little frosting.

20:21.220 --> 20:22.698
Somebody ruined your cake,

20:22.722 --> 20:25.609
and I wanna know
who could be that thoughtless.

20:25.633 --> 20:28.374
Was it you? Or you?! Who was it?

20:28.398 --> 20:30.436
Mom, please,
you're embarrassing me.

20:30.460 --> 20:33.939
You. You look like a girl
who enjoys her frosting.

20:33.963 --> 20:37.212
No! No, I didn't touch it.

20:37.236 --> 20:40.215
It's just a cake, for god sakes.
Will you please just cut it?

20:40.239 --> 20:41.717
Mrs. Van De Kamp...

20:41.741 --> 20:43.919
Open your mouth.
I wanna smell your breath.

20:43.943 --> 20:45.951
It wasn't me! It was Barbie.

20:45.975 --> 20:47.453
Barbie!

20:49.479 --> 20:51.897
What the hell
is wrong with you?!

20:51.921 --> 20:55.431
Now it's ruined!
Everything is ruined!

21:04.394 --> 21:06.742
Um...

21:06.766 --> 21:08.974
You can just...
Leave that there,

21:08.998 --> 21:13.268
and I'll, um...
Clean it up later.

21:19.609 --> 21:22.257
Xiao-Mei, what are you
doing in our bed?

21:22.281 --> 21:25.260
I said she could sleep
in there from now on.

21:25.284 --> 21:27.638
It's got the bathroom,
you know, in case

21:27.662 --> 21:29.965
she gets sick
in the middle of the night.

21:29.989 --> 21:32.738
Well, what's wrong with the
guest bathroom? It's too far away.

21:32.762 --> 21:35.679
It's right down the hall.
Gaby, she needs her rest.

21:35.703 --> 21:37.343
And besides, that bed

21:37.367 --> 21:39.975
is much more comfortable
than the one in the guest room.

21:39.999 --> 21:41.477
Yeah, I know.

21:41.501 --> 21:44.910
That's why I had the movers
put it in here, wherewesleep.

21:44.934 --> 21:48.414
Maybe I go to my bed.

21:48.438 --> 21:50.708
Yes, xiao-Mei,
that would be good.

21:52.311 --> 21:53.441
Uh-oh.

21:56.846 --> 22:00.546
Fine. You can use our toilet.

22:06.496 --> 22:07.973
Ow! Stop kicking me.

22:07.997 --> 22:09.975
I'm just trying
to get comfortable.

22:09.999 --> 22:13.339
Yeah, in a twin? Good luck.

22:13.363 --> 22:16.311
God, I want my bed back.

22:16.335 --> 22:18.814
We'll go buy a nice big one
tomorrow

22:18.838 --> 22:22.087
and put it in here, okay? That is not the
point. We are a week into this pregnancy,

22:22.111 --> 22:25.090
and you're already putting
xiao-Mei's needs before mine.

22:25.114 --> 22:28.454
Well, she's the priority now.
She's the mother of my child.

22:29.719 --> 22:33.328
Like hell she is. That ismyegg.

22:33.352 --> 22:35.369
You know what I mean.
She's the...

22:35.393 --> 22:37.332
Oven, Carlos. The oven.

22:37.356 --> 22:39.505
A well-cared-for,
well-paid oven.

22:39.529 --> 22:41.507
It came out wrong.
I'm sorry, okay?

22:41.531 --> 22:44.061
Now can we just get some sleep?

22:46.566 --> 22:48.674
Ohh! Babe, I'm sorry.

22:48.698 --> 22:50.716
I swear.
I swear I didn't mean to.

22:50.740 --> 22:53.449
My leg just cramped up.

22:53.473 --> 22:55.953
Where are you going?
That's my pillow!

22:57.547 --> 22:59.385
Good night.

23:03.553 --> 23:05.863
Matthew!

23:22.902 --> 23:24.750
Mom, come on.

23:24.774 --> 23:27.458
Oh, my god.
What are you doing in there?

23:27.482 --> 23:28.754
Danielle, is that you?

23:28.778 --> 23:30.756
My mom found out
what we did to Caleb.

23:30.780 --> 23:33.889
She flipped out and locked me in
here. Don't worry. I'll get you out.

23:33.913 --> 23:35.896
Be really careful, okay?
Please, okay?

23:35.920 --> 23:38.063
I've never seen her
like this before.

23:38.087 --> 23:40.065
She's seriously lost it
this time.

23:40.089 --> 23:42.568
I know a little something
about psycho moms.

23:42.592 --> 23:45.130
Trust me, I'll be fine.

23:51.631 --> 23:53.138
Hey.

23:53.162 --> 23:56.181
Cleaning up after the big party?

23:56.205 --> 23:58.865
Yeah.

24:01.471 --> 24:02.748
You know, it's late.

24:02.772 --> 24:05.420
Why don't you, uh,
go to bed and, you know,

24:05.444 --> 24:08.431
let Julie and I help you
with that in the morning?

24:08.455 --> 24:11.927
Oh, that's okay.
I can't sleep anyway.

24:11.951 --> 24:14.660
Are you... okay?

24:14.684 --> 24:17.603
I take it you heard
what happened.

24:17.627 --> 24:20.706
Yeah, when you flip out
in front of the pep squad,

24:20.730 --> 24:23.569
word travels fast.

24:23.593 --> 24:25.741
It was the oddest sensation.

24:25.765 --> 24:28.443
I was fine,
and everything was fine,

24:28.467 --> 24:32.478
and then suddenly I was
on the outside of my body

24:32.502 --> 24:35.581
watching a woman
who looked like me

24:35.605 --> 24:38.023
becoming a raving maniac.

24:38.047 --> 24:41.186
Bree, I'm worried about you.
Do...

24:41.210 --> 24:43.689
Do you think that you should
see someone? Oh, no, I'm fine.

24:43.713 --> 24:47.097
I'm just tired, that's all.
I just need a long rest,

24:47.121 --> 24:49.595
and then I'm gonna be
as good as new.

24:49.619 --> 24:54.469
Okay, well, then why
don't you stop and go to bed?

24:54.493 --> 24:58.504
Because, um, I can't sleep
just yet.

24:58.528 --> 24:59.775
Why not?

24:59.799 --> 25:01.476
Because when I sleep, I dream,

25:01.500 --> 25:03.679
and when I dream,
I keep seeing Andrew's face

25:03.703 --> 25:05.180
in that rearview mirror.

25:05.204 --> 25:08.053
Okay, what are you
talking about?

25:08.077 --> 25:11.717
Andrew, um...

25:11.741 --> 25:13.281
Didn't run away.

25:15.585 --> 25:22.097
I, um, dropped him off
in the middle of nowhere,

25:22.121 --> 25:24.600
told him that I couldn't
be around him anymore,

25:24.624 --> 25:27.102
and then...

25:27.126 --> 25:28.626
I drove off.

25:34.163 --> 25:37.150
So I just need a little time
to forget what I've done,

25:37.174 --> 25:40.206
and then I can sleep again.

25:42.572 --> 25:43.612
Hey.

25:48.718 --> 25:50.726
You know, I am not even tired.

25:50.750 --> 25:57.230
So... why don't I stay up
and help you?

25:58.557 --> 26:00.687
That would be nice.

26:27.717 --> 26:30.766
Thank you.

26:36.826 --> 26:37.873
Hello?

26:37.897 --> 26:40.706
Hey, you. How you doing?

26:40.730 --> 26:42.848
Hey! Great.

26:42.872 --> 26:47.582
Great. How's Atlantic city?
Are you, um, winning some money?

26:47.606 --> 26:49.114
Oh, I'm about even.

26:49.138 --> 26:51.586
Actually, I'm heading back
into the casino right now

26:51.610 --> 26:53.158
to try my luck again. Yeah?

26:53.182 --> 26:54.960
You're quite a gambler.

26:56.245 --> 26:58.724
Where's Jerry?

26:58.748 --> 27:01.727
Uh, Jerry?

27:01.751 --> 27:04.670
He... he's right here.
Hey, honey, how are the kids?

27:04.694 --> 27:06.981
Great. Great.
They're in the day care room.

27:07.005 --> 27:10.075
I'm... looking at 'em right now.

27:10.099 --> 27:12.377
Hey, why don't you
walk in there and, um,

27:12.401 --> 27:15.380
put 'em on the phone with me
so I can say hi?

27:15.404 --> 27:17.012
Okay. Sure.

27:17.036 --> 27:19.214
First, can I talk to Jerry?

27:19.238 --> 27:21.647
Why do you wanna talk to Jerry?

27:21.671 --> 27:24.750
Well, just, you know, say hello.
It's been a long time.

27:30.820 --> 27:32.627
Wow, man, that is weird.

27:32.651 --> 27:35.130
Can you hear...
Do you hear that car alarm?

27:35.154 --> 27:37.963
Uh... no.

27:37.987 --> 27:40.666
It's strange,
because I can hear it here

27:40.690 --> 27:43.238
andthrough the phone.

27:43.262 --> 27:46.146
Whoa. That's weird kind of feedback,
you know?

27:46.170 --> 27:48.143
Physics can be spooky that way.

27:48.167 --> 27:50.145
Listen, I gotta go. I gotta go.

27:50.169 --> 27:52.147
Ed is talking to me, and, um,

27:52.171 --> 27:54.149
I'll call you back later?

27:54.173 --> 27:55.180
Um, okay.

27:55.204 --> 27:56.982
Okay, bye.

27:57.006 --> 27:58.376
Bye, honey.

28:11.821 --> 28:13.799
9-1-1.
Is this an emergency?

28:13.823 --> 28:15.100
I think so.

28:15.124 --> 28:18.411
My neighbor, Paul young,
has been threatening me.

28:18.435 --> 28:20.405
Is he there right now?

28:20.429 --> 28:21.807
No.

28:21.831 --> 28:23.809
Ma'am, until he actually
does something,

28:23.833 --> 28:25.811
there's nothing we can do.

28:25.835 --> 28:27.813
Well, I won't live in fear
anymore.

28:27.837 --> 28:29.815
If you people refuse
to confront him,

28:29.839 --> 28:32.209
I guess I'll just have to
do it myself.

28:51.831 --> 28:54.780
No, Edie, wait.
Um, I don't wanna fight.

28:54.804 --> 28:56.787
I know that we've had
our differences,

28:56.811 --> 28:58.744
but, you know, we had
a friendship going there,

28:58.768 --> 29:01.286
and I just think we owe it
to ourselves

29:01.310 --> 29:03.288
to talk about what happened.

29:03.312 --> 29:06.752
What's there to talk about?
It happened.

29:06.776 --> 29:08.754
I walked down to your house...

29:08.778 --> 29:11.126
I had a
watering can... What?

29:11.150 --> 29:13.298
Filled it with gasoline and...

29:13.322 --> 29:16.031
Boom! Laughed my ass off.

29:16.055 --> 29:18.503
Okay, wait.
Could you just swallow?

29:18.527 --> 29:20.205
'Cause I couldn't really...
What you were saying...

29:20.229 --> 29:21.736
And that was basically it.

29:21.760 --> 29:23.738
One of the best days of my life.

29:23.762 --> 29:25.740
Well, see, you were chewing,

29:25.764 --> 29:27.918
and so I didn't really
hear what you said.

29:27.942 --> 29:29.915
Could you just say it again?

29:29.939 --> 29:32.918
I burnt your house down.
It was great. What do you want?

29:32.942 --> 29:34.920
So, uh, y-you then a-admit

29:34.944 --> 29:39.014
burning down my house
on purpose?

29:46.355 --> 29:48.333
You're wearing a wire,
aren't you?

29:48.357 --> 29:49.764
Huh?

29:49.788 --> 29:52.237
Open that blouse. What?

29:52.261 --> 29:53.899
Open that blouse!

29:53.923 --> 29:55.871
Aah!

29:56.826 --> 29:58.804
You can't outrun me, Mayer!

29:58.828 --> 30:00.946
I'm in the best shape
of my life!

30:00.970 --> 30:03.508
Well, good, then you'll be
prime meat picking

30:03.532 --> 30:05.210
when you go to jail!
You give it!

30:05.234 --> 30:06.944
Bite me!

30:09.378 --> 30:11.857
Aha!

30:11.881 --> 30:13.919
No! No!

30:13.943 --> 30:15.390
Ow!

30:15.414 --> 30:16.922
Ow!

30:19.488 --> 30:23.048
What the hell? Huh.

30:24.453 --> 30:25.800
Aah!

32:07.226 --> 32:10.175
Nine months
of long nights on the couch

32:10.199 --> 32:13.129
loomed before Gabrielle...

32:14.703 --> 32:19.544
And she had decided she would
not take it lying down.

32:19.568 --> 32:24.108
So she dipped into her supply
of forbidden perfumes...

32:25.414 --> 32:29.354
Determined
that in this battle...

32:29.378 --> 32:34.078
She would be the one to
come out smelling like a Rose.

32:36.025 --> 32:38.003
I think I take nap now.

32:38.027 --> 32:40.357
Yeah, sure, knock yourself out.

32:44.433 --> 32:48.443
Aah!

32:58.407 --> 33:00.077
Honey?

33:05.614 --> 33:07.164
Boys?

33:10.489 --> 33:12.689
Anybody home?

33:15.664 --> 33:17.751
Hey, Mrs. McCluskey, excuse me.

33:17.775 --> 33:21.146
You haven't seen
Lynette around, have you?

33:21.170 --> 33:24.149
She's not home. She's not
answering her cell phone.

33:24.173 --> 33:26.120
She packed up the kids
and the puppy and left.

33:26.144 --> 33:27.612
Packed 'em up? Why?

33:27.636 --> 33:30.115
She followed you
to Atlantic city.

33:30.139 --> 33:32.457
She knows about
your other woman.

33:32.481 --> 33:37.021
Boy, you're just lucky
you're not my husband.

33:44.353 --> 33:46.023
Hi.

33:55.033 --> 33:57.011
Okay, first, let me say,

33:57.035 --> 33:59.465
I'm really sorry
about the yellowjackets.

34:01.540 --> 34:04.789
And... also, no matter how mad
I am about what you did,

34:04.813 --> 34:07.392
I don't want to see you
go to prison.

34:07.416 --> 34:11.126
So I came with a solution.

34:11.150 --> 34:14.129
Why don't you just come forward
and tell the police

34:14.152 --> 34:17.601
that you saw some vagrant
lurking by my garage

34:17.626 --> 34:19.603
with a can of gasoline?

34:19.628 --> 34:24.208
And if you do that,
then I'll destroy the tape.

34:24.233 --> 34:27.080
And then the insurance company
will pay the claim.

34:27.103 --> 34:28.473
Nobody gets hurt.

34:28.496 --> 34:30.667
Does that sound good?

34:32.571 --> 34:34.119
Come closer.

34:34.143 --> 34:36.112
Oh, uh...

34:42.681 --> 34:45.659
Take your stinking deal
and shove it.

34:45.684 --> 34:47.331
Edie...

34:47.356 --> 34:49.333
Every time something bad
happens to me,

34:49.358 --> 34:51.335
you're standing nearby.

34:51.360 --> 34:53.638
Well, I've had it.

34:53.661 --> 34:55.639
No more pretending
to be friends.

34:55.664 --> 34:58.743
When I get outta here,
I'm gonna destroy you.

34:58.767 --> 35:03.208
Okay, I'm just gonna think
that this is the meds talking,

35:03.232 --> 35:05.750
and I'll come back tomorrow.

35:05.774 --> 35:07.852
Don't bother.

35:07.876 --> 35:10.215
Okay, Edie, I'm in trouble here.

35:10.239 --> 35:12.717
Oh, I'm sure you'll turn on
the waterworks,

35:12.741 --> 35:14.719
and the whole neighborhood
will come running.

35:14.743 --> 35:16.221
They always do.

35:16.245 --> 35:18.693
That's not true. Sure, it is.

35:18.717 --> 35:21.726
You never miss an opportunity
to play the victim,

35:21.750 --> 35:23.728
and you think just because

35:23.752 --> 35:26.831
everybody always comes
to your rescue,

35:26.855 --> 35:29.103
it means that you're loved.

35:29.127 --> 35:30.875
Well, it doesn't.

35:30.899 --> 35:34.279
It means that you're helpless.

35:34.303 --> 35:36.881
Now get out.

35:36.905 --> 35:39.235
Just get out.

35:48.277 --> 35:49.594
Hey there.

35:49.618 --> 35:51.526
Hi.

35:51.550 --> 35:54.859
So you given any thought
to staying at my place?

35:54.883 --> 35:58.603
Oh, yeah, that. Um...

35:58.627 --> 36:00.665
Look, I really appreciate
the offer,

36:00.689 --> 36:02.867
but I think I'm gonna
have to pass.

36:02.891 --> 36:04.609
Really? Yeah.

36:04.633 --> 36:07.217
I think it's best. I don't
wanna get a rep around here

36:07.241 --> 36:09.214
for being a charity case,
you know?

36:09.238 --> 36:11.216
Well, I didn't mean it
that way...

36:11.240 --> 36:13.518
Just one friend
helping out another.

36:13.542 --> 36:17.782
I know, but I can figure
this out on my own.

36:17.806 --> 36:19.906
At least I'm gonna try.

36:21.410 --> 36:25.230
You know, I'm stronger than
people give me credit for.

36:25.254 --> 36:26.531
I really am.

36:26.555 --> 36:29.694
Well, if there's
anything I can do...

36:29.718 --> 36:33.668
You know what would be nice?

36:33.692 --> 36:37.272
Why don't you just stop over
for coffee sometime?

36:37.296 --> 36:38.743
Okay.

36:38.767 --> 36:40.745
I mean, that is after I get

36:40.769 --> 36:42.747
running water
and electricity again...

36:42.771 --> 36:44.749
And a coffeemaker.

36:51.780 --> 36:54.659
I hope you're happy.
That poor girl can hardly even

36:54.683 --> 36:57.362
come upstairs now
because of you.

36:57.386 --> 37:00.465
Carlos, stop with the dance.
It's already in the wallpaper.

37:00.489 --> 37:03.928
Now I swear, if anything happens
to that kid because of you...

37:03.952 --> 37:06.331
Oh, it's perfume, not toxic gas.

37:06.355 --> 37:07.832
Why are you acting this way?

37:07.856 --> 37:09.834
Because I see
the writing on the wall,

37:09.858 --> 37:11.976
and it scares the hell
out of me.

37:12.000 --> 37:13.438
Meaning what?

37:13.462 --> 37:15.440
From the second
xiao-Mei got pregnant,

37:15.464 --> 37:18.688
you have found a million and one
ways to tell me that

37:18.712 --> 37:21.416
that baby is more important to
you than me. Oh, come on, Gaby.

37:21.440 --> 37:23.418
No! Men can't help it.

37:23.442 --> 37:25.750
When they become fathers,
they become lousy husbands,

37:25.774 --> 37:27.297
and some wives don't mind,

37:27.321 --> 37:29.294
but you didn't marry
one of those women.

37:29.318 --> 37:31.796
I don't think I can sleep
in here tonight.

37:31.820 --> 37:34.250
The air's
just a little too toxic.

37:42.991 --> 37:46.371
She kick you out, too?

37:46.395 --> 37:48.373
Marriage is complicated,
xiao-Mei.

37:48.397 --> 37:50.375
You'll find that out someday.

37:50.399 --> 37:54.439
You feel like watching
some trashy American TV?

37:57.306 --> 37:58.723
I make you sandwich.

37:58.747 --> 38:00.725
Roast beef.

38:00.749 --> 38:02.527
Oh, man.

38:02.551 --> 38:04.859
Gaby's got me
on this health kick thing.

38:04.883 --> 38:06.870
She'll kill me
if I eat red meat.

38:06.894 --> 38:09.455
I will not tell.

38:18.296 --> 38:19.726
Taste good?

38:22.401 --> 38:23.401
Real good.

38:25.474 --> 38:29.354
Matthew, wake up.
I have your breakfast.

38:29.378 --> 38:31.356
I might be furious with you,

38:31.380 --> 38:33.880
but never let it be said
that I'm cruel.

38:35.614 --> 38:37.601
I advise you not to charge
this door,

38:37.625 --> 38:42.497
because I am not in the mood
for any unpleasantness.

38:42.521 --> 38:44.569
Matthew?

38:44.593 --> 38:47.732
Matthew?

38:47.756 --> 38:48.873
Aah!

38:55.003 --> 38:57.990
Jeez, Danielle! I thought you
were just gonna steal the key.

38:58.014 --> 39:00.066
Let's just get out of here.

39:17.456 --> 39:19.434
Mother, Matthew and I

39:19.458 --> 39:21.936
are running away together,
and we're never coming back.

39:21.960 --> 39:26.811
If you want me to be happy,
you won't try to find us.

39:26.835 --> 39:30.415
Living in that house with you
was like being in a prison.

39:30.439 --> 39:33.347
You drove me to do this, so I
hope you'll blame yourself.

39:33.371 --> 39:35.701
Have a nice life. Danielle.

39:41.580 --> 39:42.927
Hello.

39:42.951 --> 39:44.929
My name is Bree Van De Kamp,

39:44.953 --> 39:49.063
and I'd like to admit myself
for psychiatric observation.

39:49.087 --> 39:51.566
All right,
what seems to be the problem?

39:51.590 --> 39:55.390
I think I'm about to have
a nervous breakdown.

40:02.971 --> 40:05.750
Damn it!

40:10.108 --> 40:12.408
What the hell?

40:18.987 --> 40:21.887
That psychotic bitch.

40:54.452 --> 40:55.960
There was no confrontation.

40:55.984 --> 40:58.141
Felicia tillman's the one
who made the call.

40:58.165 --> 40:59.964
She's the anonymous tip.

40:59.988 --> 41:01.866
Let's just go over there
right now.

41:01.890 --> 41:03.568
I guarantee you,

41:03.592 --> 41:06.549
the woman is having a cocktail,
laughing her ass off.

41:06.573 --> 41:09.944
We're not going anywhere yet,
sir. Ahem.

41:09.968 --> 41:13.478
Yes, I know
there's blood everywhere.

41:13.502 --> 41:15.480
She probably got it from a pig

41:15.504 --> 41:18.584
so she can vandalize
everything I own.

41:19.878 --> 41:21.486
Sergeant...

41:21.510 --> 41:24.458
What is it?

41:24.482 --> 41:27.162
Put your hands
where I can see 'em.

41:33.822 --> 41:36.572
Oh, man, she's good.

41:39.628 --> 41:42.607
It's a shocking moment
for each of us,

41:42.631 --> 41:47.581
that moment we realize
we are all alone in this world.

41:48.837 --> 41:53.637
The family we take for granted
could one day abandon us.

41:56.184 --> 41:59.664
The husband we trust
so implicitly

41:59.688 --> 42:01.718
might betray us...

42:03.692 --> 42:09.774
The daughter we love so deeply
perhaps won't return to us.

42:09.798 --> 42:13.928
And then we could end up
all by ourselves.

42:16.064 --> 42:21.546
Of course, some see great value
in going it alone.

42:21.570 --> 42:23.217
For example...

42:23.241 --> 42:25.219
Sorry about the dust,
Mrs. Huber.

42:25.243 --> 42:28.230
We don't get too many tourists
this far up the mountain.

42:28.254 --> 42:29.724
First snows come,

42:29.748 --> 42:32.226
and this place
is completely cut off.

42:32.250 --> 42:34.228
Dropping off the face
of the earth...

42:34.252 --> 42:36.230
Now that's what I call
a vacation.

42:37.656 --> 42:38.633
I'm sorry.

42:38.657 --> 42:41.157
Oh.

42:44.032 --> 42:47.042
Sometimes I'm just all thumbs.
